item.title: Package "c" does not exist [SOLVED]
item.dc:creator: @Rawox Rawox
item.description:
@Rawox wrote:

[quote=“sk8rdude461, post:1, topic:441719”]While trying to add RandQM’s Agility to my Delta server. I encountered one error that he didn’t help me solve

It said package “c” could not be found in the code:

for (int agilityObject : c.acc.agilityObstacles) { if (objectID == agilityObject) { c.acc.handleAgilityObstacles(objectID); } }

In case 132.

I’ve tried doing this:

for (int agilityObject : c.agilityObstacles) { if (objectID == agilityObject) { c.handleAgilityObstacles(objectID); } }
Which then said "agilityObstacles and handleAgilityObstacles did not exist.
And also this:

for (int agilityObject : agilityObstacles) { if (objectID == agilityObject) { handleAgilityObstacles(objectID); } }

Same non existent error.

I followed the 100% Exactly.
If someone could help I’d love it.[/quote]
If you’re just using regular Delta, it won’t work. He repackaged his source, so unless you’re using his exact released source then, you won’t be able to just copy + paste.
